            "id": "s_l1_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "More than a List 📦",
            "content": "Arrays are great for lists, but what if you want to describe a **specific thing**?\n\nLike a User (name, age, email) or a Car (brand, model, year)."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l1_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "Are arrays good for labeling specific data points?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "Yes, index numbers are clear",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "No, we need names not numbers",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "You don't want to remember that `user[2]` is the email. You want `user.email`."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_3",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "The Object 🏷️",
            "content": "An **Object** stores data in **Key-Value pairs**.\n\nUse curly braces `{ }`.",
            "codeSnippet": "let car = {\n  type: 'Fiat',\n  model: '500',\n  color: 'white'\n};",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_4",
            "type": "tip",
            "title": "Properties 🏷️",
            "content": "## Keys\n\nThe names on the left (`type`, `model`) are called **Properties** or **Keys**.\n\nThe data on the right are **Values**."
        },
